The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Bribe remand
                                                                                                               Bribe remand
                            
	Shimla, Feb. 23: Drug controller Shamsher Singh Thakur, who was caught accepting a bribe from a pharmaceutical company yesterday, has been remanded in police custody till February 27.         
	Thakur was today produced in a Solan court, which rejected his bail application.        
	Weve secured a police remand for questioning, said DSP, A.P. Singh.        
	The counsel for the accused said Thakur had been falsely implicated and the cash allegedly recovered from him was found in someone elses car. Weve moved a fresh application for his release on Monday, he said.                                                                                                                                                                           
